## `<file-level: DDL statements>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-schema-2 -->

### Purpose
The exact DDL executed at mkfs time. All five tables + the unique index on `(parent, name)`. Pinned verbatim so regeneration reproduces byte-identical SQL — changing DDL shape without changing this block is a bug the trace will catch.

### Postconditions
- Executing these statements on an empty SQLite DB produces the v1 schema.
- `PRAGMA integrity_check` on a freshly executed schema returns `"ok"`.

### Implementation Notes

```python
DDL = """
CREATE TABLE schema_version (
    version INTEGER NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,
    chunk_size INTEGER NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE nodes (
    inode INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    parent INTEGER REFERENCES nodes(inode),
    name TEXT,
    kind TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (kind IN ('file', 'dir', 'symlink')),
    mode INTEGER NOT NULL,
    uid INTEGER NOT NULL,
    gid INTEGER NOT NULL,
    size INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    atime_ns INTEGER NOT NULL,
    mtime_ns INTEGER NOT NULL,
    ctime_ns INTEGER NOT NULL,
    nlink INTEGER NOT NULL
);

CREATE UNIQUE INDEX nodes_parent_name
    ON nodes (parent, name)
    WHERE parent IS NOT NULL;

CREATE TABLE blobs (
    inode INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES nodes(inode) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    chunk_id INTEGER NOT NULL,
    data BLOB NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (inode, chunk_id)
);

CREATE TABLE xattrs (
    inode INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES nodes(inode) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    value BLOB NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (inode, name)
);

CREATE TABLE symlinks (
    inode INTEGER PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES nodes(inode) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    target BLOB NOT NULL
);
"""
```

The `ON DELETE CASCADE` clauses drive inode-GC at the SQL level — deleting a node row deletes its blobs, xattrs, and symlink row in the same transaction. `ROOT_INODE` is inserted separately by `mkfs.py` so its `parent` can be NULL.

